DOM (document object model)
--It is mainly used in web development used to interact and manipulate(change) the html document

--when the web page loaded , the browser created DOM of the webpage

--when the html file is loaded into the browser , the js directly cannot understand the html document directly


DOM : it is basically the representation of the same html document but in a tree-like structure composed of object

key points:
1.structure : the DOM represents the structure of html document as a tree. Each node in the elements , an attribute or text
2.manipulation : using js  , you can interact with elements (buttons, paragraphs) on the web page , changing the content , styles , can add or remove elements
3.event handling: you can handle the interactions ,like click or pressing the button
4.W3C world wide web consortium

